&lt;p&gt;The United States is set to begin a fresh round of high-level diplomacy with Iran this weekend in Pakistan, with Vice President JD Vance leading the American delegation, the White House confirmed on Wednesday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt said President Donald Trump is &amp;ldquo;dispatching his negotiating team&amp;rdquo; to Islamabad, marking the first in-person engagement between the two sides since a temporary ceasefire was reached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Vance To Lead US Delegation&lt;/h3&gt;
